articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The source said the handovers would take place under Egyptian supervision but did not specify the release date.
articles.title: Mediators agree swap of Palestinian prisoners for Israeli hostages' bodies, source says

articles.author: Olena Harmash, Tom Balmforth, Yuliia Dysa
articles.description: Ukraine said on Wednesday it was set to approve a framework minerals deal with the United States but that its success would depend on talks with President Donald Trump.
articles.title: Ukraine set to sign minerals deal, Trump confirms Zelenskiy visit

articles.author: Yimou Lee, Ben Blanchard
articles.description: Taiwan's defence ministry on Thursday reported a surge in Chinese military activity the previous day, but officials said they did not detect any live-fire exercises in a drill zone off the island's southwestern coast.
articles.title: Taiwan details surge in Chinese military activity, did not detect live fire

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: President Donald Trump on Wednesday declined to comment in response to a question about whether the United States would ever allow China to take control of Taiwan by force.
articles.title: Trump declines to answer question about China and Taiwan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday announced a reversal of concessions given to Venezuela by his predecessor Joe Biden more than two years ago.
articles.title: Trump orders termination of oil deal with Venezuela

articles.author: Anna Mehler Paperny
articles.description: Canada deported more people last year to hit its highest annual level of removals in about a decade, overwhelmingly deporting people whose refugee claims were rejected, data obtained by Reuters showed.
articles.title: Canada deports more people, predominantly those rejected for refugee status

articles.author: James Oliphant
articles.description: The White House on Wednesday denied reporters from Reuters and other news organizations access to President Donald Trump’sfirst cabinet meeting in keeping with the administration’s new policy regarding media coverage.
articles.title: White House bars AP, Reuters and other media from covering Trump cabinet meeting

articles.author: Olivia Le Poidevin
articles.description: The UN Human Rights Chief accused Israel on Wednesday of showing an unprecedented disregard for human rights in its military actions in Gaza and said Hamas had violated international law.
articles.title: Israel has shown 'unprecedented disregard for human rights' in Gaza, UN human rights chief says

articles.author: Brendan Pierson, John Kruzel
articles.description: Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts paused a federal judge's order requiring the Trump administration to pay foreign aid funds to contractors and grant recipients.
articles.title: US Supreme Court Roberts pauses federal judge's order on Trump administration foreign aid funding

articles.author: Elizabeth Piper
articles.description: British Prime Minister Keir Starmer urged the United States on Wednesday to provide a security "backstop" to any future European peacekeepers in Ukraine, saying only that would offer Kyiv a lasting peace rather than a temporary ceasefire.
articles.title: UK's Starmer says only U.S. 'backstop' can secure lasting Ukraine peace
